<paragraph blockId="0.[151,651,1263,1324]" box="[151,279,1298,1324]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,271,1298,1324]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURES 2–4" captionStartId-0="1.[151,255,1964,1988]" captionStartId-1="2.[151,269,993,1017]" captionTargetBox-0="[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetBox-1="[383,1220,166,969]" captionTargetId-0="figure-172@1.[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetId-1="figure-422@2.[364,1224,121,969]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Megalyra baltica Poinar and Shaw n. sp. in Baltic amber. Length of specimen, 6.60 mm. A. Left lateral view. B. Right subdorsal view. C. Ventral view showing antenna. D. Dorsal view showing sculpturing on mesosoma." captionText-1="FIGURES 2–4. Megalyra baltica Poinar and Shaw n. sp. in Baltic amber. 2. Forewing. Bar = 0.72 mm. 3. Hind wing. Bar = 0.66 mm. 4. Antenna. Bar = 0.63 mm." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Figs. 
<docIssue box="[226,236,1298,1324]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">1</docIssue>
–4
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1373,2020]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
The fossil is well preserved and complete except the right antenna and the last 2 metatarsal segments on the left leg are missing (
<figureCitation box="[248,377,1408,1431]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-172@1.[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megalyra baltica Poinar and Shaw n. sp. in Baltic amber. Length of specimen, 6.60 mm. A. Left lateral view. B. Right subdorsal view. C. Ventral view showing antenna. D. Dorsal view showing sculpturing on mesosoma." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Figs. 1A–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1373,2020]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Female. Body length, 
<quantity box="[436,521,1442,1465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="6.6">6.6 mm</quantity>
; Color silver- black (
<figureCitation box="[748,834,1442,1465]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-172@1.[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megalyra baltica Poinar and Shaw n. sp. in Baltic amber. Length of specimen, 6.60 mm. A. Left lateral view. B. Right subdorsal view. C. Ventral view showing antenna. D. Dorsal view showing sculpturing on mesosoma." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); head and thorax (and abdomen to a lesser extent) covered with fine, white, erect setae; setal tufts absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1373,2020]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Head. Broad, rounded, wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[632,717,1512,1535]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-172@1.[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megalyra baltica Poinar and Shaw n. sp. in Baltic amber. Length of specimen, 6.60 mm. A. Left lateral view. B. Right subdorsal view. C. Ventral view showing antenna. D. Dorsal view showing sculpturing on mesosoma." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
); length 
<quantity box="[813,912,1512,1535]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.2" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="0.92">0.92 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity box="[991,1090,1512,1535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.70 mm</quantity>
; face width 
<quantity box="[1221,1320,1512,1535]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.2" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="0.92">0.92 mm</quantity>
; head covered with irregularly positioned small to large foveae (except for longitudinal row of small foveae extending between dorsal ocelli); distance between foveae mostly shorter than their diameters; compound eyes large, prominent, inner margins convex, slightly divergent above; eyes surrounded by band-like border bearing large foveae; eyes bearing microscopic fine, short erect setae; maximum diameter of compound eye 
<quantity box="[880,979,1650,1673]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.1" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="0.81">0.81 mm</quantity>
; ocelli large, maximum diameter of lateral ocellus 
<quantity box="[233,332,1685,1708]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="0.14">0.14 mm</quantity>
; distance between lateral ocellus and compound eye 
<quantity box="[896,994,1685,1708]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="0.22">0.22 mm</quantity>
; distance between lateral ocelli 
<quantity box="[1334,1432,1685,1708]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="0.22">0.22 mm</quantity>
; antennae longer than head and mesosoma combined (
<figureCitation box="[730,824,1720,1743]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-172@1.[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megalyra baltica Poinar and Shaw n. sp. in Baltic amber. Length of specimen, 6.60 mm. A. Left lateral view. B. Right subdorsal view. C. Ventral view showing antenna. D. Dorsal view showing sculpturing on mesosoma." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Figs. 1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[837,853,1720,1743]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–4" captionStartId="2.[151,269,993,1017]" captionTargetBox="[383,1220,166,969]" captionTargetId="figure-422@2.[364,1224,121,969]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2–4. Megalyra baltica Poinar and Shaw n. sp. in Baltic amber. 2. Forewing. Bar = 0.72 mm. 3. Hind wing. Bar = 0.66 mm. 4. Antenna. Bar = 0.63 mm." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">4</figureCitation>
), filiform; scape (antennal segment 1) widest; pedicel (antennal segment 2) shortest; flagellomere 1 (antennal segment 3) longest; remaining flagellomeres sub-equal in length; length of first flagellomere 
<quantity box="[444,542,1789,1812]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="0.29">0.29 mm</quantity>
; width of first flagellomere 
<quantity box="[840,938,1789,1812]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1373,2020]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,152,452]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Mesosoma (
<figureCitation box="[328,456,1824,1847]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-172@1.[158,1429,493,1952]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megalyra baltica Poinar and Shaw n. sp. in Baltic amber. Length of specimen, 6.60 mm. A. Left lateral view. B. Right subdorsal view. C. Ventral view showing antenna. D. Dorsal view showing sculpturing on mesosoma." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Figs. 1B–D</figureCitation>
). Front margin of mesoscutum convex; length of mesoscutum 
<quantity box="[1123,1221,1824,1847]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="0.95">0.95 mm</quantity>
; maximum width of mesoscutum 
<quantity box="[291,390,1858,1881]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.76" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.76">1.76 mm</quantity>
; scutellum separated from large triangular axillae by punctate groves; propodeum with four large rectangular foveae in mid-line of horizontal face; forewing length 5.0 mm; wing membrane lightly infumate throughout; small stigma present; most veins highly sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[711,776,1928,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–4" captionStartId="2.[151,269,993,1017]" captionTargetBox="[383,1220,166,969]" captionTargetId="figure-422@2.[364,1224,121,969]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2–4. Megalyra baltica Poinar and Shaw n. sp. in Baltic amber. 2. Forewing. Bar = 0.72 mm. 3. Hind wing. Bar = 0.66 mm. 4. Antenna. Bar = 0.63 mm." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); Rs curving up almost to wing margin; Rs-M reaching wing margin; 1A continuing almost to wing margin; M-Cu1 prominent; Cu1 prominent; M straight; 1mcu prominent; hind wing lightly infumate throughout (
<figureCitation box="[519,583,1997,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–4" captionStartId="2.[151,269,993,1017]" captionTargetBox="[383,1220,166,969]" captionTargetId="figure-422@2.[364,1224,121,969]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2–4. Megalyra baltica Poinar and Shaw n. sp. in Baltic amber. 2. Forewing. Bar = 0.72 mm. 3. Hind wing. Bar = 0.66 mm. 4. Antenna. Bar = 0.63 mm." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); length 
<quantity box="[677,775,1997,2020]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="3.8">3.80 mm</quantity>
; Rs departing from Sc-R at 42% of wing length; all tibia bear- ing single spine (spur) at apex; metabasitarsus with row of comb-like setae on ventral surface; hind femur swollen, maximum length 
<quantity box="[293,391,186,209]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.20 mm</quantity>
; maximum width 
<quantity box="[584,682,186,209]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="0.62">0.62 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,152,452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
Metasoma. Silvery, smooth except for few scattered erect setae; length 
<quantity box="[953,1051,221,244]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.50 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity box="[1128,1225,221,244]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.43" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="1.43">1.43 mm</quantity>
; hypopygium short, ovipositor length 
<quantity box="[339,437,256,279]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="5.2">5.20 mm</quantity>
; ovipositor tip with at least 15 teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,152,452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Ratios: Face width/eye size, 1.14; first flagellomere-length/width, 2.42; length first flagellomere/ length second flagellomere, 0.70; length hind femur/width hind femur, 0.54; head width/ head length, 1.85; length mesoscutum/width mesoscutum, 0.54; length metasoma/length body, 0.53; length metasoma/ width metasoma, 1.82; maximum diameter ocellus/ distance between ocelli, 0.64; ovipositor length/ body length, 0.79; distance between lateral ocelli/ distance between lateral ocellus and compound eye, 1.00.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
